(1037, 1, '2011-08-18 14:50:24', '2011-08-18 21:50:24', 'By Eric Laughlin - Telegraph correspondent\r\n<div style="float: left; font-size: .9em; width: 372px; margin:0 10px 10px 0"><img src="http://folsomtelegraph.com/uploads/inline/1312838446_39b2.jpg" alt="" width="334" height="222" border="0" />\r\ncourtesy Forever Land, a tribute to Michael Jackson, is the headlining act at Saturday Night in the Park on Aug. 13.</div>\r\nIt’s by far El Dorado Hills’ largest community event and is expected to draw as many as 5,000 people.\r\n\r\nSaturday Night in the Park was originally developed as a daytime family event in 2002, but scorching temperatures eventually led organizers to move the festivities toward dusk.\r\n\r\nThis year’s event will feature entertainment for all ages, including two live bands, wine tasting, free giveaways, activities for children, and a local business showcase.\r\n\r\n“We see it as a wonderful way to close out our summer concert series and give family and friends an opportunity to get together,” said the event’s organizer Mike Cottrell. “We also expect to have about 50 business booths.”\r\n\r\nEl Dorado Hills Chamber of Commerce president Debbie Manning is organizing the business showcase and said the opportunity will help residents learn about their nearby merchants.\r\n\r\n“Everybody knows the importance of buying local,” she said. “But a lot of people work out of town and don’t have the opportunity to know the great businesses in their community.”\r\n\r\nSaturday Night in the Park is slated for 4:30 to 9:30 p.m. Saturday, Aug. 13, at the community park at 1021 Harvard Way. Cottrell said the local band Poster Child is the opening act, followed by a Michael Jackson tribute band by the name of Foreverland.\r\n\r\n* * *', 'Live music, wine tasting to highlight Saturday Night in the Park (Folsom Telegraph)', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'live-music-wine-tasting-to-highlight-saturday-night-in-the-park-folsom-telegraph', '', '', '2011-08-18 14:50:24', '2011-08-18 21:50:24', '', 0, 'http://foreverlandsf.com/?p=1037', 218, 'post', '', 0),
